         <div xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300"><!-- p5l2-r11 -->
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Hd1e108">Rubrica 11</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De prouidencia et preconsiliatione belli</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-d1e114">
              De prouidentia et 
              <lb ed="#K" n="50"/>preconsiliatione belli. Rubrica. 11
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-d1e121">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Rd1e118">SEneca in prouerbiis:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Qd1e125">Diu preparandum 
              <lb ed="#K"/>est bellum vt vincas celerius.</quote> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-d1e133">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Rd1e132">Ualerius maximus libro 7. titulo.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Qd1e137">sapienter
              <lb ed="#K"/>dicta aut facta: Scipio aphricanus 
              <lb ed="#K"/>turpe esse aiebat in re mili<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>tari 
              dicere non putabam: quia videlicet 
              <lb ed="#K"/>explorato et excisso consilio
              <lb ed="#K"/>que ferro aguntur administrari 
              <lb ed="#K"/>oportere arbitrabatur: summa 
              <lb ed="#K"/>ratione inemendabilis: est 
              <lb ed="#K"/>enim error qui violentie martis 
              <lb ed="#K"/>committitur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-d1e155">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Rd1e156">Uegetius de re militari libro 3. titulo 9.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Qd1e159">Ad rem pertinet qualis 
              <lb ed="#K"/>ipse aduersarius vel eius comites 
              <lb ed="#K"/>qui sint nosse: vtrum temerarii: 
              <lb ed="#K"/>an cauti an audaces: an
              <lb ed="#K"/>timidi scientes artem bel<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>licam: 
              vel ex casu temere pug<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>nantes
              Que gentes cum hiis 
              <lb ed="#K"/>fortes que ignauie sint: 
              <lb ed="#K"/>nostra auxilia cuius fidei quarum 
              <lb ed="#K"/>sunt virium. Quos animos illius 
              <lb ed="#K"/>copie: quos habeat noster exercitus. 
              <lb ed="#K"/>Que pars sibi magis victoriam 
              <lb ed="#K"/>repromittat: ex huiusmodi enim co<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>gitaminibus 
              virtus augetur: aut 
              <lb ed="#K"/>frangitur. Dux vigilans sobrius 
              <lb ed="#K"/>prudens tanquam de ciuili causa inter 
              <lb ed="#K"/>partes iudicaturus adhibito con<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>silio 
              de suis et aduersarii copiis
              <lb ed="#K"/>iudicet: et si multis rebus superior 
              <lb ed="#K"/>inuenitur: optimum sibi non dif<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>ferat 
              inire conflictum. Si vero 
              <lb ed="#K"/>aduersarium intelliget potiorem 
              <lb ed="#K"/>certamen publicum vitet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-d1e206"> 
              <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Rd1e207">12. titulo.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Qd1e208">Ipsa 
                  <pb ed="#K" n="213-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#K" n="a"/>
              <lb ed="#K" n="1"/>die qua certaturi sunt milites 
              <lb ed="#K"/>quid sentiant diligenter explo<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>ra 
              nam fidutia vel formido
              <lb ed="#K"/>ex vultum verbis incessu mori<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>bus 
              cernitur et caetera. et noueris te 
              <lb ed="#K"/>oportere differre si exercitati bel<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>latores 
              metuunt dimicare.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-d1e222">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Rd1e227">Cassiodorus: epistolarum. libro i. epistola 16.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Qd1e226">Res 
              <lb ed="#K"/>preliorum bene disponitur quotiens
              <lb ed="#K"/>in pace tractatur. Munitio quippe 
              <lb ed="#K"/>tunc efficitur preualida si diu<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>rna 
              fuerit cogitatione roborata.
              <lb ed="#K"/>Male constructio loci: tunc queritur 
              <lb ed="#K"/>quando iam pericula formidantur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-d1e240"> 
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Rd1e245">Libro 3. epistola 49.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Qd1e242">Munitio captanda 
              <lb ed="#K"/>semper in ocio est: quia tunc ma<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>le
              queritur quoniam necessaria iudicatur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-d1e250">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Rd1e259">Isydorus solliloquiorum. libro 2. capitulo 20.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Qd1e254">Imp<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>rouisus 
              hostis fortiter opprimit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-d1e260">
              <lb ed="#K"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Rd1e271">Andreas capellanus pape in<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>nocenti 
              iiii. libro de disuasiones 
              <lb ed="#K"/>vxoris.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d99300-Qd1e264">Considera vires tuas 
              <lb ed="#K"/>antequem hostem ad eas: ne suc<lb ed="#K" break="no"/>cumbas 
              et sera sit penitentia 
              <lb ed="#K"/>cum non erit qui adiuuet 
              <lb ed="#K"/>vel succurrat.</quote>
            </p>
         </div>
